<p><a name=".22Core.22_language_standards" id=".22Core.22_language_standards"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Fortran&amp;action=edit&amp;section=29" title="Edit section: &quot;Core&quot; language standards">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">"Core" language standards</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFANSI_X3.9-1966">ANSI X3.9-1966. <i>USA Standard FORTRAN</i>. American National Standards Institute.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=USA+Standard+FORTRAN&amp;rft.aulast=ANSI+X3.9-1966&amp;rft.au=ANSI+X3.9-1966&amp;rft.pub=American+National+Standards+Institute&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Fortran"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Informally known as FORTRAN 66.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFANSI_X3.9-1978">ANSI X3.9-1978. <i>American National Standard – Programming Language FORTRAN</i>. American National Standards Institute.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=American+National+Standard+%E2%80%93+Programming+Language+FORTRAN&amp;rft.aulast=ANSI+X3.9-1978&amp;rft.au=ANSI+X3.9-1978&amp;rft.pub=American+National+Standards+Institute&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Fortran"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Also known as <a href="/wiki/ISO_standard" title="ISO standard" class="mw-redirect">ISO</a> 1539-1980, informally known as FORTRAN 77.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFANSI_X3.198-1992_.28R1997.29">ANSI X3.198-1992 (R1997). <i>American National Standard – Programming Language Fortran Extended</i>. American National Standards Institute.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=American+National+Standard+%E2%80%93+Programming+Language+Fortran+Extended&amp;rft.aulast=ANSI+X3.198-1992+%28R1997%29&amp;rft.au=ANSI+X3.198-1992+%28R1997%29&amp;rft.pub=American+National+Standards+Institute&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Fortran"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Informally known as Fortran 90.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFISO.2FIEC_1539-1:1997">ISO/IEC 1539-1:1997. <i>Information technology – Programming languages – Fortran – Part 1: Base language</i>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Information+technology+%E2%80%93+Programming+languages+%E2%80%93+Fortran+%E2%80%93+Part+1%3A+Base+language&amp;rft.aulast=ISO%2FIEC+1539-1%3A1997&amp;rft.au=ISO%2FIEC+1539-1%3A1997&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Fortran"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Informally known as Fortran 95. There are a further two parts to this standard. Part 1 has been formally adopted by ANSI.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFISO.2FIEC_1539-1:2004">ISO/IEC 1539-1:2004. <i>Information technology – Programming languages – Fortran – Part 1: Base language</i>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Information+technology+%E2%80%93+Programming+languages+%E2%80%93+Fortran+%E2%80%93+Part+1%3A+Base+language&amp;rft.aulast=ISO%2FIEC+1539-1%3A2004&amp;rft.au=ISO%2FIEC+1539-1%3A2004&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Fortran"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Informally known as Fortran 2003.</li>
</ul>
